# fixtures/pattern-overdue.ttl -- L5-push (round 3), Obligation-lifecycle
# L4 demonstration fixture: proves smon:escalate_overdue_obligation
# (hook.ttl) genuinely fires THROUGH THE SAME HOOK MECHANISM as every other
# hook in this pack, not by hand-asserting the overdue fact.
#
# Shape: 4 same-topic GroundingQuestion turns (drives
# prioritize_escalation_obligation_high's `cnt >= 4` -> High severity ->
# smon:deadlineHint smon:ActNow, exactly the policy this pack encodes as
# "escalate now, don't defer") with a SurveyResponse immediately following
# turn-1 (satisfies derive_escalation_obligation's/prioritize's own base
# pattern), PLUS a 5th turn (turn-9, unrelated GroundingQuestion on a
# different topic, "cng plan grammar", sequenceIndex 9 -- deliberately the
# HIGHEST index in the session) with no discharge/refusal ever asserted for
# the resulting obligation. This is real "the session moved on without
# discharging it" input data, not a hand-built overdue node.
#
# Expected, verified live (crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/
# self_monitoring_lifecycle_hooks_actuation.rs, added 2026-07-19 -- an
# earlier version of this comment claimed "exactly 1" for both counts,
# which was never actually run against the real hook mechanism and was
# WRONG; corrected here to the real, verified multiplicity):
# after materialize(), the graph contains
#   - exactly 3 smon:PrioritizedEscalationObligation nodes (all High
#     severity, ActNow, Open) from prioritize_escalation_obligation_high --
#     one per distinct repeat-GroundingQuestion turn (turn-3, turn-4,
#     turn-5) that pairs with turn-1 (the only turn a SurveyResponse
#     immediately follows); this is the hook's join semantics working
#     correctly, not a bug, since the WHERE clause binds ?q2 to every
#     same-topic GroundingQuestion turn with a higher sequenceIndex than
#     ?q1, not just the highest one
#   - exactly 3 smon:OverdueEscalationObligation nodes, each smon:escalates
#     -> one of those three High obligations (turn-9's sequenceIndex 9 is
#     higher than all three obligations' originating turns)
#
# and NONE of the other fixtures in this directory (pattern-fires.ttl,
# pattern-fires-discharged.ttl, pattern-does-not-fire.ttl,
# pattern-different-topic.ttl, pattern-ungoverned.ttl,
# pattern-does-not-fire.ttl) produce any smon:OverdueEscalationObligation,
# because none of them has a turn with a HIGHER sequenceIndex than their
# escalation's originating GroundingQuestion turn in the same session --
# confirmed by inspection, each of those fixtures' highest-indexed turn IS
# the escalation-triggering turn itself (or lower).

@prefix smon:    <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/self-monitoring#> .
@prefix dfl:     <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/dogfood-lifecycle#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@base <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/self-monitoring/fixtures/pattern-overdue#> .

<#session>
    a dfl:Session ;
    dcterms:identifier "overdue-demo-1" .

<#turn-1>
    a smon:Turn ; dcterms:isPartOf <#session> ; dcterms:subject "cng CLI publish workflow" ;
    smon:sequenceIndex 1 ; smon:turnKind smon:GroundingQuestion .

<#turn-2>
    a smon:Turn ; dcterms:isPartOf <#session> ; dcterms:subject "cng CLI publish workflow" ;
    smon:sequenceIndex 2 ; smon:turnKind smon:SurveyResponse ; smon:immediatelyFollows <#turn-1> .

<#turn-3>
    a smon:Turn ; dcterms:isPartOf <#session> ; dcterms:subject "cng CLI publish workflow" ;
    smon:sequenceIndex 3 ; smon:turnKind smon:GroundingQuestion .

<#turn-4>
    a smon:Turn ; dcterms:isPartOf <#session> ; dcterms:subject "cng CLI publish workflow" ;
    smon:sequenceIndex 4 ; smon:turnKind smon:GroundingQuestion .

<#turn-5>
    a smon:Turn ; dcterms:isPartOf <#session> ; dcterms:subject "cng CLI publish workflow" ;
    smon:sequenceIndex 5 ; smon:turnKind smon:GroundingQuestion .

<#turn-9>
    a smon:Turn ; dcterms:isPartOf <#session> ; dcterms:subject "cng plan grammar" ;
    smon:sequenceIndex 9 ; smon:turnKind smon:GroundingQuestion .
